Frequently Asked Questions

What is the median home price in New York?
Homes for sale in New York have a median listing price of $885K. Some of these homes are Hot Homes, meaning they're likely to sell quickly.
How long do homes stay on the market in New York?
Most homes for sale in New York stay on the market for 176 days and receive 2 offers. In the past month, 32241 homes have been sold in New York. The median price per square foot in New York has increased by 3.1% over the past year.
What are some of the most popular neighborhoods in New York?
Popular neighborhoods include Maplewood, Fresh Meadows, West Orange, Flushing, Bayside, Queens, Forest Hills, Upper East Side, Jamaica, Queens Village, Staten Island, Brooklyn, Astoria, Teaneck, and Whitestone.
How often does Redfin update their new listings?
Most of our new listings in New York are updated every 5 minutes so you can see new homes as soon as they come on the market. Learn More
